          <h2>Home</h2>
         
        

  <h3>Welcome to our site!</h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">Lewisham Nexus Service is a registered Charity working in the London Borough of Lewisham since 1993. We believe that the people we support need us to fully understand the community within which they live and that the people who support them are linked into and have good knowledge of the resources available in their community.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">We are registered with the Care Quality Commission; at our last inspection in December 2014 we were deemed to be good in all standards and outstanding in Leadership. To access our inspection report please go to <a href="/media/14875/cqc-report.pdf" title="Report">our report</a>.<br /> <br /> Our aim, through the support we offer is to empower people to shape and take control of their own lives, providing opportunities for people to develop and improve their lifestyles.</p>
<h4>Our services include:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Supported Living</li>
<li>Community Based Support Service</li>
<li>Community and Employment Focused Day Services </li>
<li>A Café that offers paid work, training and work experience to people with learning disabilities.</li>
<li>All Star Trainers, a group of learning disabled trainers who deliver training to people with and without disabilities</li>
</ul>
<p>Services can be purchased through individual/personal budgets and direct payments.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.cqc.org.uk/location/1-123154158?referer=widget3" target="_blank" title="Lewisham Nexus Service"><img width="269" height="323" src="/media/8364/widget.jpg" alt="Widget"/></a> </p>
